      1          /**
      2           *  @file       
      3           *
      4           *  @brief      Allows to interact with your project allowing to debug your system at different levels
      5           *
      6           *  @details    EXECUTE METHOD APIS:
      7           *              The API004Debug module provides commands to execute global methods of your projects
      8           *              and allows to receive feedbacks , if any, from the method itself, such as the
      9           *              return value of the function.
     10           *              The methods have to be listed in a table described in the prv file and , for each
     11           *              method, you need to insert a label (a string to mark the method), the pointer to the method
     12           *              and a Signature value that contains the information of the data types for the input and ouput
     13           *              of the method.
     14           *              The Api uses 2 opcodes for this purpose: one to publish the information of all the listed methods
     15           *              and another one to execute the method with the required input parameter values.
     16           *              If the executed method has a return value, the value will be published in the feedback packet
     17           *
     18           *              To Enable this module you have to use the SystemConfig_prm file since the definition value is also
     19           *              used by the "Reveal_prv" file to allow to correct use of the parser functionalities
     20           *  @copyright  Copyright 2021 Whirlpool Corporation.  All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL.
     21           */
